class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₂}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₂, u₂}</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">J</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">K</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.ColimitCocone\">ColimitCocone</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Category.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.flip\">flip</a></span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Cones.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.Cocone\">Cocone</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a functor `F` and a collection of colimit cocones for each diagram `X ↦ F X k`, we can stitch\nthem together to give a cocone for the diagram `F`.\n`combinedIsColimit` shows that the new cocone is colimiting, and `evalCombined` shows it is\n(essentially) made up of the original cocones.\n","docLink":