cones for each diagram `X ↦ F X k`, we can stitch\nthem together to give a cone for the diagram `F`.\n`combinedIsLimit` shows that the new cone is limiting, and `evalCombined` shows it is\n(essentially) made up of the original cones.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.combineCones","kind":"def","line":70,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.combineCones","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.lean#L70-L85"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.evaluationJointlyReflectsLimits\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">evaluationJointlyReflectsLimits</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">J</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">J</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₂}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₂, u₂}</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">J</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Cones.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.Cone\">Cone</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">K</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/IsLimit.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.IsLimit\">IsLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Products/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.evaluation\">evaluation</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Cones.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.mapCone\">mapCone</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/IsLimit.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.IsLimit\">IsLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The evaluation functors jointly reflect limits: that is, to show a cone is a limit of `F`\nit suffices to show that each evaluation cone is a limit. In other words, to prove a cone is\nlimiting you can show it's pointwise limiting.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.evaluationJointlyReflectsLimits","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.evaluationJointlyReflectsLimits","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.lean#L49-L67"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/FunctorCategory/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.colimit.ι_desc_app_assoc\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">colimit</span>.<span class=\"name\">ι_desc_app_assoc</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">J</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">J</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn